   I have been having an occasional problem where the message

ns_resp: Out of memory

comes out on the console, gradually increasing in frequency until the name
server finally dies (causing everything on the system to break due to a
known bug in 4.3BSD that prevents the backup /etc/hosts file from being
used once the name server has been accessed; and no, I can't fix it because
we don't have sources for 4.3 on this machine). Does anyone know what
causes this to happen and if there is anything I can do about it? 
We are running 4.3BSD on an Integrated Solutions 68020-based machine,
if it matters.

--Greg
